<h2 id="a-react-redux-tutorial-from-idea-to-deployment">A React Redux tutorial from idea to deployment.</h2>

<p>I just released a <a href="(https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLWRvoIK5KFymTrMa7mzvxuxl5ei_MyeF7)">set of youtube videos</a> that cover building a full site in React with Redux from start to finish.
I wanted to a tutorial on React so I decided to do something a little bit different.
I decided to build an entire site, basically screen record the whole the thing and
then deploy it, open source, it and in the process try to build something actually useful.</p>

<h2 id="using-create-react-app">Using ‚ÄúCreate React App‚Äù</h2>

<p>For the tutorial I started with Facebook‚Äôs ‚ÄúCreate React App‚Äù, the reason is that
it did not have a backend and it does not come with Redux wired up by default. So as part of the tutorial
I was able to focus on client side and add Redux, build some actions, and then finally
add routing using react-router-dom.</p>

<h2 id="ok-so-where-is-it">Ok So where is it</h2>

<p>The actual site is here - <a href="http://www.fpvbuildcalc.com">it‚Äôs called ‚Äúfpvbuildcalc.com‚Äù</a>.</p>

